HEADWORD: Physophoræ
<hw>Phy*soph"o*r⟦ae⟧</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>fy^sa</grk> a bellows + <grk>fe`rein</grk> to
bear.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of Siphonophora, furnished
with an air sac, or float, and a series of nectocalyces. See
